00106         // Traverses the callers or callees of this function
00107         // A call graph may have multiple nodes for a same function, each node may have multiple in or out edges.
00108         // So the iterator actually works on two levels:
00109         //    level 1: iterate through all nodes for a given function
00110         //    level 2: iterate through all in or out edges for each node, return the source or destination node
00111         class iterator
00112         {
00113                 // direction in which the iterator is going
00114                 //SgIncidenceDirectedGraph::EdgeDirection iterDir;
00115                 // side of an edge that we're going to be following
00116                 //SgIncidenceDirectedGraph::EdgeDirection edgeDir;
00117                 
00118                 // Direction in which the iterator is going (fw: from callers to callees, bw: from callees to callers)
00119                 public:
00120                 //typedef enum direction {fw=0, bw=1};
00121                 enum direction {fw=0, bw=1};
00122                 protected:
00123                 direction dir;
00124                 
00125                 std::set<SgGraphNode*>::iterator itn;
00126                 std::set<SgDirectedGraphEdge*> edges; // The current SgGraphNode's (*itn) incoming or outgoing edges
00127                 std::set<SgDirectedGraphEdge*>::iterator ite; // The current edge in edges
00128                         
00129                 // The set the SgGraphNodes that have already been visited by this iterator
00130                 // used to eliminate duplicates
00131                 std::set<SgGraphNode*> visitedCGNodes;
00132                         
00133                 const CGFunction* func;
00134                 
00135                 // =true if this iterator has reached the end of all the edges and =false if not
00136                 bool finished;
00137                         
00138                 public:
00139                 iterator()
00140                 {
00141                         finished = true;
00142                 }
00143                         
00144                 iterator(const CGFunction* const func, direction dir)
00145                 {
00146                         this->func = func;
00147                         this->dir = dir;
00148                         
00149                         finished=false;
00150                         
00151                         itn = func->cgNodes.begin();
00152                         if(dir == fw) edges = func->graph->computeEdgeSetOut(*itn);
00153                         else          edges = func->graph->computeEdgeSetIn(*itn);
00154                         ite = edges.begin();
00155                         
00156                         advanceToNextValidPoint();
00157                 }
00158                 
00159                 // Returns a reference to CGFunction that matches the current SgGraphNode that this iterator refers to,
00160                 // pulling the reference from the given set of CGFunctions
00161                 const CGFunction* getTarget(std::set<CGFunction> &functions)
00162                 {
00163                         //printf("getTarget finished=%d\n", finished);
00164                         SgGraphNode* target = (dir == fw ? (*ite)->get_to() : (*ite)->get_from());
00165                         ROSE_ASSERT(isSgFunctionDeclaration(target->get_SgNode()));
00166                         
00167                         // Compiler-generated functions do not appear as nodes in the call graph
00168                         if(isSgFunctionDeclaration(target->get_SgNode())->get_file_info()->isCompilerGenerated()) return NULL;
00169                         
00170                         // Find the CGFunction in functions that matches the target SgGraphNode
00171                         for(std::set<CGFunction>::const_iterator it = functions.begin(); it!=functions.end(); it++)
00172                         {
00173                                 //printf("    iteration. current: %s isCompilerGenerated=%d, target=%s, isCompilerGenerated=%d\n", (*it).get_name().str(), (*it).get_declaration()->get_file_info()->isCompilerGenerated(), target->functionDeclaration->get_name().str(), target->functionDeclaration->get_file_info()->isCompilerGenerated());
00174                                 // If the target SgGraphNode can be found in the current CGFunction
00175                                 if((&(*it))->cgNodes.find(target) != (&(*it))->cgNodes.end())
00176                                         return &(*it);
00177                         }
00178                         
00179                         //printf("getTarget returning NULL\n");
00180                         
00181                         // If we can't find it, return NULL
00182                         ROSE_ASSERT(!"Error finding the target function of a call graph edge when the target is not compiler generated!");
00183                         return NULL;
00184                 }
00185                 
00186                 // Returns the function that this iterator is currently referring to
00187                 Function getTarget()
00188                 {
00189                         SgGraphNode* target = (dir == fw ? (*ite)->get_to() : (*ite)->get_from());
00190                         ROSE_ASSERT(isSgFunctionDeclaration(target->get_SgNode()));
00191                         Function result(isSgFunctionDeclaration(target->get_SgNode()));
00192                         return result;
00193                 }
00194                 
00195                 void operator ++( int )
00196                 {
00197                         ite++;
00198 
00199                         advanceToNextValidPoint();
00200                 }
00201                 
00202                 // If the current <itn, ite> pair refers to a specific CallGraph node, does nothing.
00203                 // otherwise, advances the <itn, ite> pair until it does refer to a specific CallGraph node
00204                 void advanceToNextValidPoint()
00205                 {
00206                         //printf("Function::iterator::advanceToNextValidPoint()\n");
00207                         // Loop for as long as ite is not pointing to a valid node and hasn't reached the end of the node list
00208                         while(1)
00209                         {
00210                                 // If ite is the last incoming/outgoing edge of the current SgGraphNode
00211                                 if(ite == edges.end())
00212                                 {
00213                                         //printf("Function::iterator::advanceToNextValidPoint() while()\n");
00214                                         // Advance to the next SgGraphNode in cgNodes
00215                                         itn++;
00216                                         
00217                                         // If this is not the last SgGraphNode in cgNodes
00218                                         if(itn != func->cgNodes.end())
00219                                         {
00220                                                 // Set edges to the incoming/outgoing edges of the new SgGraphNode and set ite to refer to the first edge
00221                                                 if(dir == fw) edges = func->graph->computeEdgeSetOut(*itn);
00222                                                 else          edges = func->graph->computeEdgeSetIn(*itn);
00223                                                 ite = edges.begin();
00224                                         }
00225                                         // otherwise, leave the loop since this iterator has reached the end
00226                                         else
00227                                         {
00228                                                 finished=true;
00229                                                 break;
00230                                         }
00231                                 }
00232                                 // Else, if it is not the last edges
00233                                 else
00234                                 {
00235                                         SgGraphNode* target = (dir == fw ? (*ite)->get_to() : (*ite)->get_from());
00236                                         // If we've already seen this node
00237                                         if(visitedCGNodes.find(target) != visitedCGNodes.end())
00238                                                 ite++;
00239                                         // Else, we have a valid node. Record that we've visited it and break out since we've found a valid upstream/downstream node
00240                                         else {
00241                                                 visitedCGNodes.insert(target);
00242                                                 break;
00243                                         }
00244                                 }
00245                         }
00246                 }
00247                 
00248                 bool operator == (const iterator& that)
00249                 {
00250                         // if either iterators are finished, then they're equal iff the other is finished, ignoring any other fields
00251                         if(finished) return that.finished;
00252                         else if(that.finished) return finished;
00253                                 
00254                         // otherwise, they're equal only if all their other members are equal
00255                         return (dir == that.dir) &&
00256                                (itn == that.itn) &&
00257                                (edges == that.edges) &&
00258                                (ite == that.ite) &&
00259                                (func == that.func);
00260                 }
00261                 
00262                 bool operator != (const iterator& that)
00263                 { return !((*this) == that); }
00264         };
